verses.text: Then came the daughters of Zelophehad , the son of Hepher , the son of Gilead , the son of Machir , the son of Manasseh , of the families of Manasseh the son of Joseph : and these \add are\add* the names of his daughters ; Mahlah , Noah , and Hoglah , and Milcah , and Tirzah.
And they stood before Moses , and before Eleazar the priest , and before the princes and all the congregation , \add by\add* the door of the tabernacle of the congregation , saying ,

Our father died in the wilderness , and he was not in the company of them that gathered themselves together against the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* in the company of Korah ; but died in his own sin , and had no sons.

Why should the name of our father be done away from among his family , because he hath no son ? Give unto us \add therefore\add* a possession among the brethren of our father.\f + \fr 27.4 \ft done…: Heb. diminished\f*
And Moses brought their cause before the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*. \p
¶ And the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* spake unto Moses , saying ,

The daughters of Zelophehad speak right : thou shalt surely give them a possession of an inheritance among their father’s brethren ; and thou shalt cause the inheritance of their father to pass unto them.
And thou shalt speak unto the children of Israel , saying , If a man die , and have no son , then ye shall cause his inheritance to pass unto his daughter.
And if he have no daughter , then ye shall give his inheritance unto his brethren.
And if he have no brethren , then ye shall give his inheritance unto his father’s brethren.

And if his father have no brethren , then ye shall give his inheritance unto his kinsman that is next to him of his family , and he shall possess it: and it shall be unto the children of Israel a statute of judgment , as the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* commanded Moses. \p
¶ And the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* said unto Moses , Get thee up into this mount Abarim , and see the land which I have given unto the children of Israel.
And when thou hast seen it, thou also shalt be gathered unto thy people , as Aaron thy brother was gathered.

For ye rebelled against my commandment in the desert of Zin , in the strife of the congregation , to sanctify me at the water before their eyes : that \add is\add* the water of Meribah in Kadesh in the wilderness of Zin. \p
¶ And Moses spake unto the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*, saying ,
Let the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*, the God of the spirits of all flesh , set a man over the congregation ,

Which may go out before them, and which may go in before them, and which may lead them out , and which may bring them in ; that the congregation of the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* be not as sheep which have no shepherd. \p
¶ And the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* said unto Moses , Take thee Joshua the son of Nun , a man in whom \add is\add* the spirit , and lay thine hand upon him;
And set him before Eleazar the priest , and before all the congregation ; and give him a charge in their sight.
And thou shalt put \add some\add* of thine honour upon him, that all the congregation of the children of Israel may be obedient.

And he shall stand before Eleazar the priest , who shall ask \add counsel\add* for him after the judgment of Urim before the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*: at his word shall they go out , and at his word they shall come in , \add both\add* he, and all the children of Israel with him, even all the congregation.
And Moses did as the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* commanded him: and he took Joshua , and set him before Eleazar the priest , and before all the congregation :
And he laid his hands upon him, and gave him a charge , as the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* commanded by the hand of Moses.
